![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/5ee3e7ae-57d7-4dde-95bc-ca6debac50c2/20240405_081526.jpg)

With WrestleMania weekend fast approaching, wrestling fans are gearing up for two nights of thrilling action, and excitement reached a fever pitch with the recent reveal of the full match order by The Wrestling Observer. From championship clashes to highly anticipated showdowns, the lineup promises to deliver an unforgettable spectacle for fans around the world.

On Night 1 of WrestleMania, fans can expect a blockbuster lineup featuring some of the biggest names in the industry.

The action kicks off with a high-stakes battle as Rhea Ripley defends her title against the formidable Becky Lynch.

The intensity continues with a Tag Title Ladder Match, followed by a family feud as Rey Mysterio teams up with Dragon Lee to take on Dominik Mysterio and Santos Escobar.

Sibling rivalry takes center stage as Jimmy Uso squares off against Jey Uso in a matchup that is sure to have fans on the edge of their seats.

The action-packed night also features a star-studded six-person tag team match, pitting Bianca Belair, Jade Cargill, and Naomi against the formidable trio of Damage CTRL.

The championship matches continue with GUNTHER defending his title against the resilient Sami Zayn, before the night culminates in a colossal showdown between two powerhouse teams.

The Rock teams up with Roman Reigns to take on the dynamic duo of Cody Rhodes and Seth Rollins in a match that promises to be nothing short of epic.

As Night 1 comes to a close, anticipation is already building for the action-packed lineup set to unfold on Night 2 of WrestleMania.

The excitement continues with Seth Rollins defending his title against Drew McIntyre in what is sure to be a hard-hitting encounter.

Tag team action takes center stage as Bobby Lashley and the Street Profits face off against Karrion Kross and A.O.P in a clash of titans.

The night also features a highly anticipated singles match between LA Knight and AJ Styles, as well as a triple threat match for the championship title featuring Logan Paul, Randy Orton, and Kevin Owens.

The Women's Championship is on the line as Iyo Sky defends her title against the formidable Bayley, before the night culminates in a blockbuster main event.

Roman Reigns puts his title on the line once again, this time facing off against the resilient Cody Rhodes in a battle for supremacy.

With the full match order now revealed, anticipation is at an all-time high as wrestling fans eagerly await the action-packed spectacle that is WrestleMania weekend. As superstars prepare to step into the ring and make history, one thing is certain: WrestleMania is set to deliver two nights of unforgettable moments, jaw-dropping surprises, and epic showdowns that will leave fans on the edge of their seats.

WM NIGHT 1:

• Rhea Ripley (c) vs Becky Lynch

• Tag Title Ladder Match

• Rey Mysterio & Dragon Lee vs Dominik Mysterio & Santos Escobar

• Jimmy Uso vs Jey Uso

• Bianca Belair, Jade Cargill & Naomi vs Damage CTRL

• GUNTHER (c) vs Sami Zayn

• The Rock & Roman Reigns vs Cody Rhodes & Seth Rollins

WM NIGHT 2:

• Seth Rollins (c) vs Drew McIntyre

• Bobby Lashley & Street Profits vs Karrion Kross & A.O.P

• LA Knight vs AJ Styles

• Logan Paul (c) vs Randy Orton vs Kevin Owens

• Iyo Sky (c) vs Bayley

• Roman Reigns (c) vs Cody Rhodes

